methods.description: Returns the cached value for a property, if one exists. This can be useful for peeking at the value of a computed property that is generated lazily, without accidentally causing it to be created.
methods.name: cacheFor

params.name: obj
params.description: the object whose property you want to check

params.name: key
params.description:
the name of the property whose cached value you want
  to return

methods.description:
Creates a shallow copy of the passed object. A deep copy of the object is returned if the optional deep argument is true.

If the passed object implements the Ember.Copyable interface, then this function will delegate to the object's copy() method and return the result. See Ember.Copyable for further details.

For primitive values (which are immutable in JavaScript), the passed object is simply returned.
methods.name: copy

params.name: deep
params.description: If true, a deep copy of the object is made.

methods.description: Generates a new guid, optionally saving the guid to the object that you pass in. You will rarely need to use this method. Instead you should call Ember.guidFor(obj), which return an existing guid if available.
methods.name: generateGuid

params.name: obj
params.description:
Object the guid will be used for. If passed in, the guid will
  be saved on the object and reused whenever you pass the same object
  again.

  If no object is passed, just generate a new guid.

params.name: prefix
params.description:
Prefix to place in front of the guid. Useful when you want to
  separate the guid into separate namespaces.

methods.description:
Returns a unique id for the object. If the object does not yet have a guid, one will be assigned to it. You can call this on any object, Ember.Object-based or not, but be aware that it will add a _guid property.

You can also use this method on DOM Element objects.
methods.name: guidFor

params.name: obj
params.description: any object, string, number, Element, or primitive

return.description: the unique guid for this instance.
